{
  "texts": [
    "The latter can be recognized as the category describing topological line defects of the 3d 2 Dijkgraaf-Witten gauge theory, or in other words the 2+1d toric code.",
    "In other words, we are enumerating different ways of choosing a non-anomalous 2 1-form symmetry of the above 3d TQFT.",
    "The simple topological line operators of the 3d TQFT are {1, e, m, ψ},with fusions e ⊗ e = m ⊗ m = ψ ⊗ ψ = 1 and ψ = e ⊗ m, and spins θ (e) = θ (m) = 1 and θ (ψ) = -1.",
    "There are precisely three choices for a non-anomalous 2 1-form symmetry:1.",
    "Choose the identity line 1 as the generator of the 2 1-form symmetry."
  ]
}